Change `"AZEN2026"` to whatever passcode you want clients-only-you-to-have. This is
a simple gate, not full authentication — good enough to keep casual visitors out of
the dashboard, but don't treat it as bank-grade security.

## Deploying (takes about 10–15 minutes, no coding needed)

**1. Create a GitHub account** (skip if you have one) at github.com.

**2. Create a new repository** on GitHub, e.g. named `azen-coaching-portal`.
Upload this entire folder's contents to that repository (GitHub's website lets you
drag-and-drop files directly — click "Add file" → "Upload files").

**3. Create a Vercel account** at vercel.com — sign up with your GitHub account,
it's free for this use case.

**4. Import the project:**
   - In Vercel, click "Add New" → "Project"
   - Select your `azen-coaching-portal` GitHub repo
   - Click "Deploy" (leave all settings as default — Vercel auto-detects Next.js)

**5. Add Vercel KV (the shared database):**
   - Once deployed, go to your project in Vercel → "Storage" tab
   - Click "Create Database" → choose "KV" (or "Upstash for Redis" if KV is renamed)
   - Follow the prompts to create it and connect it to your project
   - This automatically sets the environment variables the code needs
     (`KV_REST_API_URL`, `KV_REST_API_TOKEN`, etc.) — you don't need to type
     anything yourself

**6. Redeploy:**
   - Go to the "Deployments" tab → click the "..." menu on the latest deployment
     → "Redeploy" (this picks up the new KV connection)

**7. Done.** Vercel gives you a live URL like `azen-coaching-portal.vercel.app`.
   You can add a custom domain (e.g. `coachedbyazen.com`) later under
   Project → Settings → Domains, once you buy one from any domain registrar.

## What clients see vs. what you see

- `yourdomain.com/client` — client check-in, progress chart, and community view
- `yourdomain.com/coach` — your dashboard (behind the access code)
- `yourdomain.com/` — the role-select landing page

